"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-sport-olympics-beth-potter-triathlon-result-bronze-paris-2024-b2588725.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  Eight years ago, Potter finished 38th in the women's 10,000m on the track at the Rio Olympics but changing sports to triathlon has paid dividends  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 468, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  Beth Potter hascome a long wayfrom the athletewho morosely sipped cocktailsfrom a coconut on the Copacabana eight years ago.\", \"from\": 469, \"to\": 617, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 493, \"end\": 504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beth_Potter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Beth Potter\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beth_Potter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beth_Potter\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her career was at an inflection point after a distant 38th-place finish in the 10,000m at the RioOlympicsbut a chance meeting in McDonald's and aswitch of sports was rewardedatParis 2024with women'striathlonbronze.\", \"from\": 619, \"to\": 833, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Potterwon the test event here last yearand the world title but this season has failed to make the top step of the podium at the global level, claiming she wasarriving in Parisflying under the radar.\", \"from\": 835, \"to\": 1033, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her tactics were clear: stay in contention through the swim and stay out of trouble on the bike, where greasy cobbled sections were treacherous after heavy overnight rain.\", \"from\": 1035, \"to\": 1206, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Then she could strike on the run, where, on her day, she's the strongest athlete in the field.\", \"from\": 1208, \"to\": 1302, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But she did not count on France's Cassandre Beaugrand who, roared on by a sea of French tricolours along this made-for-Instagram course, proved just too strong.\", \"from\": 1304, \"to\": 1464, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1329, \"end\": 1335, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8927329469966409, \"rank\": 0.07844466939632197, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1338, \"end\": 1357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cassandre_Beaugrand\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cassandre Beaugrand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cassandre_Beaugrand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cassandre_Beaugrand\"}, {\"begin\": 1385, \"end\": 1391, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8521679032154684, \"rank\": 0.14957413415288895, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When she kicked for home, Potter and the silver medallist, Switzerland's Julie Derron, simply had no response as she streaked into the distance.\", \"from\": 1466, \"to\": 1610, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1525, \"end\": 1536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"score\": 0.999761718581807, \"rank\": 0.00018346146593069867, \"text\": \"Switzerland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They were both too good for me but I am super happy to come away with bronze,\\\" said Potter, who is coached by Olympic champion brothers Alistair and Jonny Brownlee, moving to their Leeds training group when she quit track and field.\", \"from\": 1612, \"to\": 1845, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1749, \"end\": 1757, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alistair_Brownlee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.336415967919022e-30, \"text\": \"Alistair\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alistair_Brownlee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alistair_Brownlee\"}, {\"begin\": 1762, \"end\": 1776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonny_Brownlee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jonny Brownlee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonny_Brownlee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonny_Brownlee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's just relief, to be honest.\", \"from\": 1847, \"to\": 1879, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This day has been in the calendar for a long time, so to come away with a medal - I am just over the moon.\", \"from\": 1880, \"to\": 1986, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Gold was on my mind but I got a medal, so there are no complaints.\", \"from\": 1988, \"to\": 2055, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a wall of noise out there, there was not one part of that course that was quiet.\", \"from\": 2056, \"to\": 2143, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have come a long way in eight years and I really feel like I did this for me and for those who believed in what I was doing switching sports.\", \"from\": 2145, \"to\": 2289, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Brownlees have been a massive part of my journey.\", \"from\": 2291, \"to\": 2345, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They are the reason I moved to the triathlon.\", \"from\": 2346, \"to\": 2391, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I train with Alistair day in, day out, and he's such a big part of my story.\", \"from\": 2392, \"to\": 2468, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I moved in with Jonny when I first moved to Leeds too.\", \"from\": 2470, \"to\": 2525, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2515, \"end\": 2520, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leeds\", \"score\": 0.9999794127379656, \"rank\": 2.0500052220828034e-05, \"text\": \"Leeds\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leeds\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leeds\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They are always the first to message me before and after races and it means so much to know that I have the support of them.\\\"\", \"from\": 2526, \"to\": 2651, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The water quality in the Seinehas been the talking point of recent days, despite the high-profile efforts of French authorities to clean it up at a reported cost of \\u00a31bn.\", \"from\": 2653, \"to\": 2823, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2762, \"end\": 2768, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8521679032154684, \"rank\": 0.14957413415288895, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's race was already delayed 24 hours and Potter and teammates Georgia Taylor-Brown, who finished sixth, and Kate Waugh went to bed last night not knowing whether they'd race in the morning.\", \"from\": 2825, \"to\": 3021, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2894, \"end\": 2914, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Taylor-Brown\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Georgia Taylor-Brown\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Taylor-Brown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Taylor-Brown\"}, {\"begin\": 2940, \"end\": 2944, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Ramsay\", \"score\": 0.9999998381968129, \"rank\": 1.6180330852184783e-07, \"text\": \"Kate\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Ramsay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Ramsay\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organisers got their wish, the race atwo-hour television showcasefor Paris's postcard landmarks, a grand stage for a French leading lady, who crossed the line on the Pont Alexander III to cheers that rumbled across the city.\", \"from\": 3023, \"to\": 3247, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3092, \"end\": 3097, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5937327666095168e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3140, \"end\": 3146, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8521679032154684, \"rank\": 0.14957413415288895, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 3194, \"end\": 3207, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_the_Great\", \"score\": 0.6418622420871944, \"rank\": 0.5579660098050843, \"text\": \"Alexander III\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_the_Great\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_the_Great\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the question remains, at what cost?\", \"from\": 3249, \"to\": 3288, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The staging of the Games has forced politicians to finally act on the embarrassing water quality of the Seine, where swimming has been banned since 1923 due to pollution levels.\", \"from\": 3290, \"to\": 3467, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3394, \"end\": 3399, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999823699001, \"rank\": 1.7629062322876286e-08, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But many of these athletes are due to race again in next week's team event - if they can stay healthy.\", \"from\": 3468, \"to\": 3570, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Taylor-Brown took a cocktail of prebiotics and probiotics and lined her stomach with Peptobismol; she'd barely caught her breath before she was gurgling mouthwash.\", \"from\": 3572, \"to\": 3735, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"France and Great Britain look the ones to beat in the team event, with Taylor-Brown and Yee likely to be the only returning members of the gold medal-winning quartet from Tokyo.\", \"from\": 3737, \"to\": 3914, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3737, \"end\": 3743, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8927329469966409, \"rank\": 0.07844466939632197, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3748, \"end\": 3761, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9903674393730247, \"rank\": 0.006903087420684043, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3908, \"end\": 3913, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9460244113086146, \"rank\": 0.05600354393889457, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Let us see what the coaches decide but hopefully I am picked, and we can go again,\\\" added Potter, who is one of over 1,000 elite athletes on UK Sport's National Lottery-funded World Class Programme, allowing them to train full-time, have access to the world's best coaches and benefit from pioneering medical support - which has been vital on their pathway to the Paris 2024 Games.\", \"from\": 3916, \"to\": 4298, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4058, \"end\": 4066, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"UK Sport\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\"}, {\"begin\": 4058, \"end\": 4066, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"UK Sport\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am going to give myself a couple of days to enjoy this and then it's about resetting and going again for the relay.\", \"from\": 4300, \"to\": 4418, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We feel like we have got a really strong team, two in the top six of the women's race proves that.\", \"from\": 4419, \"to\": 4517, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's nice to have a medal but obviously nicer to have two.\\\"\", \"from\": 4518, \"to\": 4577, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With more than \\u00a330m a week raised for Good Causes, including vital funding into elite and grassroots sport, National Lottery players support our Olympic and Paralympic athletes to live their dreams and make the nation proud, as well as providing more opportunities for people to take part in sport.\", \"from\": 4579, \"to\": 4877, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4687, \"end\": 4703, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Lottery_Heritage_Fund\", \"score\": 0.9999998554012668, \"rank\": 1.4457252612960868e-07, \"text\": \"National Lottery\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Lottery_Heritage_Fund\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Lottery_Heritage_Fund\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To find out more visit:www.lotterygoodcauses.org.uk  Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies  Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 4878, \"to\": 5161, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4982, \"end\": 4993, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0945831425432675e-16, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\"}]}]}"